=> Terraform Vs Python ==>

1. TF manages state of the infrastructure.
2. TF knows the current state also knows the difference of current state
    and your configured/desired state but Python doesn't have a state.
3. TF is idempotent but Python isn't idempotent.
4. In TF, you declared the end result (which means if you delete any block of
    configuration, entire configured block from Aws also deleted.) but In Python, You
    need to explicitly write code to delete the resources.

=> Different Use Cases for BOTO3 ==>

1. More Complex Logic Possible also can do more stuff as it's a aws library.
    Example :- Monitoring, BackUps, Scheduled Tasks.
